By UJA EMMANUEL, Makurdi A naval officer, David Igbashal, who was abducted on the 22nd February, 2020 by gunmen somewhere in Akwa Ibom State on his way home from Calabar has been confirmed dead. The Nation gathered that 11 of his alleged abductors suspected to be ritualists have been arrested by security operatives at a shrine in Agbor, Delta State. Naval officer David Igbashal was a fresh graduate from the Nigerian Defence Academy  (NDA), and was posted to Calabar port. Igbashal was from Ikyaghev Council ward of Gwer-West local government area of Benue State. (The Nation) Calabar - Gov. Ben Ayade of Cross River has lauded President Muhammadu Buhari for the appointment of Rear-Adm. Ibok-Ete Ibas as the new Chief of Naval Staff. Ayade conveyed the gratitude of his administration and people of the state in a statement made available to the News Agency of Nigeria… July 14, 2015 In "News" By George Odok   Calabar,   -    Rear Admiral Mathew Emuekpere, the Flag Officer Commanding, Eastern Naval Command (ENC), Nigerian Navy, said the command seized over 13,803 bags of smuggled rice valued at N22.8 million in the past seven months. Emuekpere disclosed this on Tuesday in Calabar, Cross River, during the… August 28, 2018 In "News" By Yahaya Isah Abuja -   The Nigerian Navy (NN) has announced new appointments and re-appointments of officers for effective and efficient service delivery. The Acting Director of Information, Naval Headquarters, Navy Capt. Suleman Dahun, disclosed this in a statement on Friday in Abuja. Those appointed, Dahun said, include: three… January 13, 2018 In "News"